‚ÄúDial this code for free bonus‚Äù scam

Q18: Will Orange or Africell ever call to ask for my PIN?

A:
No. Never.
No legitimate mobile operator will ask you for your PIN, OTP code, or password.
Any call requesting such information is a scam.

Q19: What should I do if I suspect a mobile money scam?

A:

Hang up immediately

Do not share any code

Call the official customer service lines:

Orange: 111

Africell: 111

Visit a physical mobile operator shop to confirm

Report suspicious numbers to NATCOM

Q20: What is the ‚ÄúWrong Transfer Scam‚Äù?

A:
This happens when a scammer claims they mistakenly sent you money and asks you to ‚Äúsend it back.‚Äù
In reality, no money was sent to you ‚Äî they want you to send your own money to them.

Q21: How do I protect my Mobile Money account?

A:

Use a strong PIN

Change your PIN regularly

Never share codes with anyone

Do not hand your phone to strangers

Only use registered agents

Enable SMS notifications

Ignore suspicious promos

